          <div style="opacity:0">.</div>
        </div>
      <h1>Verification Mode</h1>
      <p class="sub">
        EV424 does not judge truth/falsehood.<br />
        It verifies integrity only: reproducible match or mismatch.
      </p>
    </section>
    <section class="panel">
      <h2>What “Deterministic Verification” means</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="k">Definition</div>
          <div class="v">Same input → Same output</div>
          <p class="p">
            If the official source bytes and the input parameters are identical,
            the output receipt and SHA-256 fingerprints must reproduce identically.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="k">Scope</div>
          <div class="v">Integrity only</div>
          <p class="p">
            EV424 reports match/mismatch. It does not interpret content, intent, or meaning.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="k">Evidence boundary</div>
          <div class="v">Re-verifiable artifacts only</div>
          <p class="p">
            Outputs are closed by verification gates (e.g., SHA-256) and can be checked independently.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
          <div class="k">User experience</div>
          <div class="v">Exact-match lookup</div>
          <p class="p">
            Public search accepts only two keys: Evidence ID and PASS hash (64-hex SHA-256).
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="panel">
      <h2>Operational guarantees</h2>
      <ul class="bul">
        <li>Identical input produces identical verification results.</li>
        <li>Any mismatch is treated as a failure (change detected).</li>
        <li>No summarization, no rewriting, no “AI interpretation” in the verification result.</li>
        <li>Only receipts and re-verification methods are published (no PDF mirroring).</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="hr"></div>

      <h2>Why this matters</h2>
      <ul class="bul">
        <li>Reduces ambiguity: verification is mechanical and reproducible.</li>
        <li>Supports audits: anyone can independently re-check with the same rules.</li>
        <li>Prevents “looks fine” traps: only validated outputs are accepted.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

            <div class="motto">Accuracy(4)=Truth(2)=Life(4)</div>
